name: command
description:
The command is what eventually changes the model. Figures are asked for a command for a given request. Commands also help determine if the interaction is possible. If there is no command, or it is not executable, the UI will indicate that the interaction is not allowed.

All commands (move, drag&drop, insert, remove,....) are stored on top of a CommandStack and available for undo and redo. An draw2d.Canvas has a single command stack. Commands must be executed using the command stack rather than directly calling execute.

classes.name: Command
classes.description:
Commands are passed around throughout editing. They are used to encapsulate and combine changes to the application's model. An application has a single command stack. Commands must be executed using the command stack rather than directly calling execute.
This is required for a generic support for the undo/redo concept within draw2d.

classes.name: CommandStack
classes.description:
An implementation of a command stack. A stack manages the executing, undoing, and redoing of Commands. Executed commands are pushed onto a a stack for undoing later. Commands which are undone are pushed onto a redo stack. Whenever a new command is executed, the redo stack is flushed.

You can retrieve the current used CommandStack just by calling canvas.getCommandStack()

functions.name: init
functions.description: Create a new CommandStack objects which can be execute via the CommandStack.

functions.name: setUndoLimit
functions.description: Set the maximal undo stack size. Entries will be remove if the max. stack size has been reached.

functions.name: markSaveLocation
functions.description: Remove the undo / redo history. This is useful if the user has been save the document.

functions.name: execute
functions.description: Executes the specified Command if possible. Prior to executing the command, a draw2d.command.CommandStackEvent for {@link #PRE_EXECUTE} will be fired to event listeners. Similarly, after attempting to execute the command, an event for {@link #POST_EXECUTE} will be fired.

functions.name: startTransaction
functions.description: Opens a transaction for further multiple commands. If you execute a command all {@ #execute} calls will be ignored until you commit the current transaction.

parameters.name: commandLabel
parameters.description: the label to show for the undo/redo operation

functions.name: isInTransaction
functions.description:
Returns true if the Command Stack has an open transaction. You can start or stop a transaction with startTransactionand commitTransaction.

A transaction is one undo/redo operation.

functions.name: commitTransaction
functions.description: Commit the running transaction. All commands between the start/end of a transaction can be undo/redo in a single step.

functions.name: undo
functions.description: Undo on command from the stack and store them on the redo command stack.

functions.name: redo
functions.description: Redo a command after the user has undo a command

functions.name: getRedoLabel
functions.description: Return the label of the next REDO command.

functions.name: getUndoLabel
functions.description: Return the label of the next UNDO command.

functions.name: canRedo
functions.description: Indicates whenever a REDO is possible.

returns.description: true if it is appropriate to call {@link #redo()}.

functions.name: canUndo
functions.description: indicator whenever a undo is possible.

functions.name: addEventListener
functions.description: Adds a listener to the command stack, which will be notified whenever a command has been processed on the stack.

functions.name: on
functions.description: Adds a listener to the command stack, which will be notified whenever a command has been processed on the stack.

functions.name: removeEventListener
functions.description: Removes a listener from the command stack.

functions.name: notifyListeners
functions.description: Notifies command stack event listeners that the command stack has changed to the specified state.

classes.name: CommandStackEvent
classes.description: Event class which will be fired for every CommandStack operation. Required for CommandStackListener.

functions.name: init
functions.description: Create a new CommandStack objects which can be execute via the CommandStack.

parameters.name: details
parameters.description: the current state of the command execution

functions.name: getStack
functions.description: Return the corresponding stack of the event.

functions.name: getCommand
functions.description: Returns null or a Command if a command is relevant to the current event.

functions.name: getDetails
functions.description: Returns an integer identifying the type of event which has occurred. Defined by {@link draw2d.command.CommandStack}.

functions.name: isPostChangeEvent
functions.description: Returns true if this event is fired after the stack having changed.

functions.name: isPreChangeEvent
functions.description: Returns true if this event is fired prior to the stack changing.

classes.name: CommandStackEventListener
classes.description: Event class which will be fired for every CommandStack operation. Required for CommandStackListener.

functions.name: init
functions.description: Creates a new Listener Object

functions.name: stackChanged
functions.description: Sent when an event occurs on the command stack. draw2d.command.CommandStackEvent.getDetail() can be used to identify the type of event which has occurred.

classes.name: CommandType
classes.description:
EditPolicies should determine an Figures editing capabilities. It is possible to implement an Figure such that it handles all editing responsibility.
However, it is much more flexible and object-oriented to use EditPolicies. Using policies, you can pick and choose the editing behavior for an Figure without being bound to its class hierarchy. Code reuse is increased, and code management is easier.
